<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 94 / Labour warns on shopping centres
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Local authorities which suffered financial loss because their objections to
out-of-town shopping centres were overruled should be compensated by the
government, Mr Keith Vaz, a Labour environment spokesman, urged yesterday.
He called on Mr John Gummer, environment secretary, to follow up the recent
policy U-turn towards keeping shops in town centres by autho-rising higher
regeneration grants to areas whose once-thriving high streets had started to
resemble ghost towns.
Mr Vaz said a survey showed that, since 1989, 290 out-of-town developments
opposed by local authorities on planning grounds had been allowed on appeal
to the environment secretary.
Mr Vaz said the government's U-turn had resulted in a 'lame-duck policy'
which left councils footing the bill.
</TEXT>
