FT  12 AUG 94 / Estate agents see fall in house sales
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JAMES BLITZ
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
House sales last month fell by almost a 10th compared with July last year,
says a survey of more than 4,000 estate agency offices handling about a half
of all sales.
The survey by the Ombudsman for Corporate Estate Agents provides further
evidence of the slowdown in the housing market which has occurred since
early spring. It said potential purchasers were concerned about possible
rises in interest rates.
Sales were also 12.1 per cent lower than June this year.
Mr Peter Constable, OCEA's chairman, said: 'The magnitude of the setback
should cause concern among the authorities. While indicators show solid
recovery in most areas of the economy, it must be disconcerting for them to
see this state of a paralysis in the housing market.'
