<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 94 / The main points of C&amp;G's plan
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
C&amp;G's plan will mean that:
Borrowers will get no cash payments.
Investors - savers who are members of the society - who opened accounts
after December 31 1992 will get no cash payments.
Investors of more than two years' standing at the end of this year will get
about 13 per cent of the balance of each investment account up to a maximum
of Pounds 100,000, provided the account is still open on completion day. The
sums will be on the basis of the lower balance on either completion day or
April 20 this year. Those with more than Pounds 100 at the end of 1994 get
an extra Pounds 500.
Holders of deposit accounts who maintain an account open at the end of March
until completion day will get about 13 per cent of the lower balance of each
account on March 31 this year or the completion day. Those who had more than
Pounds 100 at the end of March will get an additional Pounds 500.
Holders of Pibs - permanent interest bearing shares - and C&amp;G Channel
Islands accounts will qualify for the flat payment of Pounds 500.
</TEXT>
