<TEXT>
Several Latin American governments are to send a mission to Haiti in an
attempt to persuade the country's military leaders to step down and prevent
a US-led military invasion to restore the exiled president, diplomats in
Port-au-Prince said yesterday, writes Canute James in Kingston.
