<HEADLINE>
FT  12 AUG 94 / Tapie fends off Credit Lyonnais
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By ALICE RAWSTHORN
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   PARIS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The beleaguered Mr Bernard Tapie yesterday won a rare victory against Credit
Lyonnais, his bank which is pressing him over his FFr1.3bn (Pounds 156m)
debts, when a Paris court decided that the left-wing entrepreneur did not
have to repay a FFr300m loan. Credit Lyonnais had claimed that Mr Tapie, a
Euro-MP, had breached the terms of the loan, which the bank made last year
to Olympique-Marseille, his football club. However the court concluded that
there was no reason to force Mr Tapie to redeem the loan given that, under
the terms of the original agreement, repayments are not due until September
this year.
