FT  11 AUG 94 / Further 207 jobs shed at Swans
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
A further 207 job losses were yesterday announced at Swan Hunter, the
Tyneside shipbuilder, The redundancies affect workers laid off since May 31.
The receivers injected a new urgency to the struggle to find a buyer for the
company by insisting that unless Constructions Mecaniques de Normandie - the
sole prospective bidder for the yard as a going concern - starts paying the
Pounds 200,000-a-month wage bill of the technical and design team by the end
of August, the team's 100 members will be made redundant.
Mr Fred Henderson of CMN said that if the design team went there was no
prospect of CMN buying Swans. 'There's no possibility of getting a workload
then,' he added.
