FT  11 AUG 94 / Trains to run to Brighton for first time in strikes
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
A third of the normal number of trains will run tomorrow and on Monday and
Tuesday next week if the expected signal workers' strike takes place,
British Rail said yesterday. It hoped to offer a 'nearly normal' service
over the weekend.
Trains will run from London to Dover, Folkestone, Brighton and Worthing for
the first time on strike days.
Routes expected to have services tomorrow, Monday and Tuesday include:
InterCity Anglia: Liverpool Street-Norwich; Ipswich to Lowestoft.
