<HEADLINE>
FT  11 AUG 94 / Refinery hit by fire to reopen next month
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By DAVID LASCELLES, Resources Editor
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Milford Haven refinery that was damaged by fire last month will resume
partial operation next month and full production in October.
Texaco, the owner, said yesterday that most of the damage was confined to
the units involved in an explosion, with other parts little affected by the
fire that followed.
Initial investigation has established that the fire was caused by the
failure of a pipe in the flare gas system which caused a release of vapour
and the subsequent explosion. The Health and Safety Executive and the
company are still clearing damaged areas for a full inspection.
The environmental group Friends of the Earth said 11 of the UK's most
hazardous industrial sites had failed to satisfy the Health and Safety
Executive over their plans for dealing with large industrial accidents.
