<HEADLINE>
FT  11 AUG 94 / World Trade News: Philips expands
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By RONALD VAN DE KROL
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   AMSTERDAM
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Philips, the Netherlands-based electronics group, is to invest Fl 500m
(Dollars 275m) in boosting production at its plant in the Dutch town of
Nijmegen, writes Ronald van de Krol in Amsterdam. The additional capacity is
expected to be ready by the end of 1996.
