Germany]'
Party leaders flatly rejected hints by Mr Kohl that a 'grand coalition'
between his Christian Democrats and the SPD might be possible. However, even
if the electoral outcome forces such a solution, yesterday's statements
suggest that the SPD will not accept the chancellor as its leader.
