<HEADLINE>
FT  10 AUG 94 / World Stock Markets: Mexico dips and rallies
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Mexican stocks ended slightly down yesterday after a mixed session dominated
by profit-taking and a technical rebound.
Traders attributed the erratic session to two periods of profit-taking split
by a technical rally. The market's volatility, they added, was enhanced
because of mixed expectations for movements in key interest rates in today's
central bank auction.
Analysts are split as to whether the bellwether 28-day Cetes, or Treasury
Bill, will see a slight fall or minor rise from last week's 15.80 per cent
rate.
Traders said profit-taking was so pronounced that the market's bellwether
stock Telefonos de Mexico (Telmex) was not the usual driving force behind
the market's overall movement. Telmex shares closed higher.
The IPC index lost a net 8.94 at 2,594.96, following a decline of 1.5 per
cent on Monday and a rise of almost 8 per cent over the course of last week.
Yesterday's turnover was a moderate 1.23bn new pesos.
Telmex 'L' series shares - those available to foreign investors - were up 4
centavos at 10.74 new pesos.
</TEXT>
