   JAKARTA
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Bank Bali, Indonesia's seventh largest bank in terms of private assets, said
its pre-tax profit for the first six months of this year rose by 2 per cent
to Rp43.44bn (Dollars 20m) compared with Rp42.50bn in last year's first
half.
Total income rose to Rp274.79bn from Rp253.27bn in the year-earlier period.
Total expenses climbed to Rp231.35bn from Rp210.81bn.
Revenues from interest rose by 11 per cent to Rp232.04bn from Rp208.81bn,
reflecting the bank's more aggressive attempts to to capture a share of
Indonesia's loan market.
