   By TRACY CORRIGAN
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Gardner Merchant, Europe's largest contract caterer, has completed a Pounds
240m financing package, part of which will be used to finance its recent
Dollars 100m (Pounds 65m) acquisition of Morrison's Hospitality Group from
Morrison Restaurants of the US, writes Tracy Corrigan.
The package includes a Pounds 155m five-year loan which will be used to
refinance existing bank borrowings, left over from the Pounds 402m
management buy-out of the company from Forte in December 1992; a Dollars
100m five-year loan to fund the Morrison's acquisition and a Pounds 20m
multi-currency working capital and guarantee facility, again over five
years.
The terms of the loans were not disclosed. The facilities were arranged by
the Royal Bank of Scotland, with five other participating banks.
