<HEADLINE>
FT  10 AUG 94 / UK Company News: Property side spurs recovery at Howard
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Howard Holdings, the property development and plant hire group, reported
pre-tax profits of Pounds 405,115 for the 12 months to April 30 - the south
London-based group's first year in the black since 1990.
Mr John Howard, chairman, attributed the recovery to property development
activities. 'Prospects continue to look good and we have now made land
purchases to sustain our level of trading,' he said.
The recession in construction and housebuilding has gone on for a long time,
said Mr Howard, but he believes the better times expected are finally
becoming a reality.
The outcome, which compared with losses of Pounds 204,749, was struck after
interest charges of Pounds 265,227 (Pounds 395,618), and reflected turnover
more than doubled to Pounds 6.38m (Pounds 3.07m).
Although plant hire had 'another difficult year' there were 'firm
indications' of a return to profits by 1995.
The dividend is 0.8p (0.5p), payable from earnings of 1.07p (0.56p losses)
per share.
The shares rose 3p to 28p.
