</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By TIM BURT
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
London International Group has made compensation payments to its former
chairman and group managing director.
The group, which manufactures Durex condoms and Marigold gloves, paid
Dollars 151,216 (Pounds 98,429) to Mr Alan Woltz, who retired as chairman in
April. Mr Robert Hall, the former group managing director, received Pounds
151,600.
The two executives retired before LIG announced net losses of Pounds 173.7m
for the year to March 31 and a Pounds 115m rescue rights issue to restore
the group's balance sheet.
The company said Mr Hall was being compensated for 'termination of
contract', while Mr Woltz's payment related to an outstanding consultancy
fee. Analysts, however, said the two men had been blamed for LIG's ambitious
diversification during the 1980s, which led to sizeable trading losses.
